article_node.title: Chappell Roanâ€™s Recent Smash Returns To Its All-Time Peak As Her Latest Debuts
article_node.summary: Chappell Roan's new single "The Subway" has become a breakout hit, topping the UK's Official Singles and Streaming charts and boosting sales of her earlier tracks. The release has propelled "The Giver" from No.5 to No.2 on the Official Physical Singles chart, marking its highest position ever, while "Good Luck, Babe!" climbed from No.12 to No.10. Although "The Subway" itself is not yet available in physical format, its popularity has indirectly lifted Roan's other songs on the charts. The single also debuted at No.3 on both the Official Singles Sales and Downloads lists, further solidifying Roan's chart dominance.
